Method behavioural specifications:
- The integer array parameter `arr` must not be null.
- The length of the integer array parameter `arr` is equal to the number of nodes in the tree.
- The integer array parameter `arr` contains the values of the nodes in the tree.
- The 2D integer array parameter `edges` must not be null.
- The length of the 2D integer array parameter `edges` is equal to the number of nodes in the tree minus 1.
- Each element in the 2D integer array parameter `edges` represents an edge between two nodes in the tree.
- The integer result is the minimum score of any possible pair of edge removals on the given tree.